note.p:
At Cambridge subscription was abolished for undergradutes in 1775;
								and bachelors of arts had only to declare themselves 'bona-fide members of the church of
							England.'

Published originally in 1778; reprinted in edition of
								&Egr;&Pgr;&Egr;&Agr;
								&Pgr;&Tgr;&Egr;&Rgr;&Ogr;&Egr;&Ngr;&Egr;&Ngr;&Tgr;&Agr;
								or Diversions of Purley, by Richard Taylor
								(1829), to which I refer. The first part of the Diversions of Purley appeared in 1786; and the second part
								(with a new edition of the first) in 1798.
